tool_description:
Wave, Weather and Tide Conditions for any spot on the Ocean Surface.

XYZ Tiles for Global Wave Conditions

https://wavebase.app
name: Wavebase
title: Wavebase

api_list.name: XYZ Map Tiles for Ocean Conditions
api_list.description:
Wavebase Global Ocean Tiles API:

Wave Signficant Height (GET): https://api.wavebase.app/v1/tiles/singleband/{variable}/{date-timeslot - YYYYMMDDHH}/0/0/0.png

e.g.: https://api.wavebase.app/v1/tiles/singleband/VHM0/2023051703/0/0/0.png 

Currently only Tile at 0/0/0 is available Free.  Contact:  info@wavebase.app for additional tiles.

api_list.name: Ocean Conditions Closest to Latitude / Longitude
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://wavebase.p.rapidapi.com/v4/conditions/search/52.8/-4.07"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "wavebase.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())

api_list.name: Bulk Current Ocean Conditions for a Set of Points
api_list.description:
​https://api.wavebase.app/v4/conditions/search/bulk

Search for current ocean conditions closest to a set of latitude/longitude points.

Returned conditions include only Wave conditions at the locations.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://wavebase.p.rapidapi.com/v4/conditions/search/bulk"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "wavebase.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.post(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())
